<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE> Biography: Robert A. Silverman </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor="#ffffff">
<img src="discussi.gif" alt="Discussion">
<hr>
<p>
<h2> Robert A. Silverman</h2>
<p>
Robert A. Silverman is a senior writer for Cowles Business Media's <i>Inside Media</i>
magazine, where he reports on new media technologies and cable television.  Silverman 
previously served as senior editor of CMP Media Inc.'s <i>Interactive Age</i> magazine, where
he helped launch the new media trade publication and edited its Content section.
<p>
Prior to joining <i>Interactive Age</i>, he covered new media and television for <i>Daily</i>
and <i>Weekly Variety</i>.  He is the co-author with Edwin Diamond of <i> White House or
Your House: Media and Politics in Virtual America</i> (MIT Press, November 1995).
<p>
His work has appeared in such publications as <i>Washington Journalism Review, National 
Journal, American Behavioral Scientist, Los Angeles Times, Philadelphia Inquirer, </i>and
<i>TV Guide</i>.  He also has provided analysis of new media and technology for CBS 
News' <i>Up to the Minute</i>CNNfn, News Talk Television, and others.
<p>
A native of New York City, Silverman is an honors graduate of New York University, where he
received a B.A. in Journalism and an M.A. in American Studies.  He is married to Kara 
Newman, a journalist for <i> Quick Nikkei Business News.</i>
<p>
<i><a href="http://www.mediacentral.com/">Inside Media</a></i> is a publication of Cowles 
Business Media, a division of Minneapolis Star-Tribune publisher Cowles Media.  Other CBM
titles include <i>Cable World, Folio, Catalog Age</i> and <i>Direct.</i>
 
</BODY>
</HTML>
