<BODY bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<img src="discussi.gif">
<hr>
<font face="arial">
<h2>CONGRESSMAN RICK WHITE</H2>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<img src="white.gif" align=left>
Representative Rick White took office in January 1995 with a pledge to make government smaller, more efficient, and more cost effective. In the 104th Congress, White will focus on reforming Congress and addressing the fundamental need to make our government more accessible and accountable to the American people. He has Iimited himself to serving no more than five terms in the U.S. House of Representatives.<p>
Recognizing the important role that technology issues, telecommunications and international trade plays in the Puget Sound region's economy, White obtained a position on the House Commerce Committee. He is assigned to the Telecommunications and Finance subcommittee and the Commerce, Trade and Hazardous Materials subcommittee. Since the Commerce Committee is classified as an "exclusive" committee by the House, it is White's only Committee assignment.<p>
Congressman White, 41, is serving his first term in elected offlee. Prior to running for Congress, White was a partner in the business law department of Seattle's largest law firm, Perkins Coie. He joined Porkins Coie in 1983 and was made a partner in 1988. In addition he has held a number of private sector jobs ranging from dock foreman to assembly line worker to grill cook.<p> 
A resident of Bainbridge Island, Representative White has a history of involvement in community service. He is a founder and director of "Books for Kids, " a literacy program that provides free books to at-risk children. He has served for many years in the YMCA's Indian Guides program and as a leader of an Explorer Scouts post. He also served as an Elder at the Rolling Bay Presbyterian Church on Bainbridge Island.<p>
Representative White emerged as a leader in the Republican Party in 1990, when he helped found the "Farm Team" to encourage young professionals to get involved in the party.  He served on the Queen Anne Community Council from 1986-88 and has served as a delegate to various district, county and state Republican conventions since 1984.<p>
Representative White was bom on November 6, 1953. He received a Bachelor of Arts in Goverment and French in 1975 from Dartmouth College.  He spent one year in a graduate program in philosophy at the Pantheon-Sorbonne in Paris, before completing his academic career with a law degree from Georgetown University in 1980.<p>
Representative White married Vikki Kennedy in 1982. The two have four children: Kathleen (12) Emily (9), Charlotte (7), and Richard (4). The family resides on Bainbridge Island.
</blockquote>
