</ul>
<p>January 18, 1996<P>
<ul>
<li><a href="/pff/mv011896.html">Are We Reliving the 1850s?</a> by <a href="/pff/people/sfellow.html#Vlahos">Michael Vlahos</a>
<li>Check out the <a href="/pff/conference/agenda.html">finalized agenda</a> for the upcoming PFF conference, <b>The New Majority:</b> Democratic Governance in a Revolutionary Age.
</ul>
<p>January 11, 1996<P>
<ul>
<li> A PFF Special Report: <a href="/pff/tr-toc.html">The Telecommunications Revolution: An American Opportunity</a>.  This report has a simple goal: to
 provide for a modern and effective government to complement market forces to speed the development of new products and services for Americans.  Reformulating the regulatory system invented in the 1930s is critical to seize the opportunities of the knowldge age--making this a "must" read!
<li>More information, including a working agenda, is available for the upcoming PFF conference, <a href="/pff/conference/newmaj.html">The New Majority</a>.
</ul>
<p>January 4, 1996<p>
<ul>
<li>The Progress and Freedom Foundation is sponsoring a conference entitled <a href="/pff/conference/agenda.html">"The New Majority: Democratic Governance in a Revolutionary Age,"</a> to be held January 22, 1996 at the Mayflower Hotel in Washington, D.C. 
</ul>
<p>January 3, 1996<P>
<ul>
